HEADWORD: Brusque
<hw>Brusque</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>brusque</ets>, from It. <ets>brusco</ets> brusque, tart, sour,
perh. fr. L. (<ets>vitis</ets>) <ets>labrusca</ets> wild (vine); or cf.
OHG. <ets>bruttisc</ets> grim, fr. <ets>brutti</ets> terror.]</ety>
<def>Rough and prompt in manner; blunt; abrupt; bluff; <as>as, a
<ex>brusque</ex> man; a <ex>brusque</ex> style</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brusqueness</ent>⟦br⟧
